Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%400g can}; pat very dry with paper towels. Halve, peel, and cut @shallot{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges.

Toss chickpeas and shallot on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, half the @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}, and @salt{1%tsp}. Roast on top rack until chickpeas are lightly crispy, ~{18-20%minutes} (it's natural for chickpeas to pop a bit as they roast!).

Remove baking sheet from oven; transfer chickpeas and shallot to a large #bowl{} to cool.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce. Halve, core, and thinly slice @Bartlett pear{1}.

In a small bowl, whisk together @cherry jam{1}, @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp}, and @olive oil{4%tbsp} until well combined. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a small, dry pan over medium-high heat. Add @sliced almonds{½%oz} and toast, stirring, until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once chickpeas and shallot have slightly cooled, transfer half the chickpeas and shallot to a plate; reserve for serving.

To bowl with remaining chickpeas and shallot, add @spinach{5%oz}, pear, and half the @feta cheese{½%cup}.

Reserve 2 TBSP dressing and set aside for serving. Add remaining dressing to bowl and toss to evenly coat. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide salad between plates or #bowls{}; top with almonds, reserved chickpeas and shallot, and remaining feta. Drizzle with reserved dressing and serve.